4. I asked the agent "what are you", it responded the right way.
Weirdly, it laughed. It shouldn't laugh at normal questions. That's mixing. 

It also said something that it shouldn't say - "измислям глупаво-неудобни обаждания, не ги пускам". No. I believe that's coming from the agent's internal idea that we've implemented earlier that it's just a part of system one (authoring system), yet there's no point in giving the user context of that. User might get confused and start wondering who, if not the app (user might not make the distinction that there's a system, inside of a system, inside of a system ad infinitum) and drift away into unnecessary conversation and burn tokens. 

Also - a reoccuring behavior, even seen in this response here is that an agent is narowwing down the context at ALL COST - asking the agent "who are you" shouldn't result in the agent saying "Да е по-скоро объркан тип, или досадно уверен?". The model is way too agressive on that. 

Upon further investigation - I asked "кой пуска пранковетв тогава" (the typo was intentional) and the agent followed the right way - "аз го подготвям, а самото обаждане се пуска от приложението автоматично". It's very interesting how the agent has adopted the identity of a subsystem. That's the right answer, but we should not have been here in the first place. Also, again after that sentence, we have "Да го направим объркано-любезен тип, или по-нагъл и досаден?"

Went one step further again with just responding "кой" in the context of "кой да направим объркано-любезен или по-нагъл..." and the agent repeated once again - "аз само сглобявам сценария" and ULTIMATELY finishes of with guess what - "Да е объркано-любезен тип, или нагъл и убеден, че е прва". I like that it at least variates, but on administrative and operational qeustions, the agent shouldn't push the prank draft directly.


